<br>
Styled attack = right hand swings and chance that offhand swings<br>
<br>
Unstyled attack = 50/50 chance of either hand swinging, with a chance of both swinging<br>
<br>
If right hand swings, then next attack goes by right hand delay, if left hand swings then next attack goes by left hand delay, and if both swing then the next attack goes by the average of the two.  When you style however, the style bonus damage is determined by the Spd of your right hand weapon.  So, as Demised said, a slow mainhand and fast offhand will add up to more damage when you DW. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
